A 52-year-old Japanese diplomat was found dead in a  pool of blood at her residence in Belem, northern Brazil, the foreign ministry  announced here Thursday
Consul Machiko Fukuzawa, 52, was found dead late Wednesday, the report  said, adding that Brazilian police had begun an investigation.
According to the report, the concierge of an apartment where Fukuzawa  lived became suspicious when he found the door to her home left open and  entered the premises. The concierge found Fukuzawa's bloodied body on the  bathroom floor.
Fukuzawa, consul at the Japanese Consulate in Belem since 1990, had  recently been reassigned to serve as first secretary at the Japanese embassy  in Uruguay, a foreign ministry official said.
No further details were available.
